==English==

===Noun===
''[[extended]] [[playing]] [[time]]'''
# (''sports'') In a one-sided sporting contest, when [[junior varsity]] players (i.e., [[second-string|second]]- and [[third-string]] players) play a majority of the game; sometimes done as a show of [[sportsmanship]] or to give younger players experience in a one-sided game.
#: ''Once the No. 1 team football built a 56-0 lead in the game against their weak opponents, the coach - wanting to spare the opponent further embarassment and sensing his own younger players needed experience - decided to give his reserves some well-deserved '''extended playing time'''.''